[3] Cases in various countries:
Philippines:
- Kalinga province. 17 Jul 2013. Dengue as of 11 Jul 2013, 958 cases; deaths (confirmed) 2; municipalities most affected: Tabuk City 687 cases, Pinukpuk 133 cases.
http://www.pia.gov.ph/news/index.php?article=181373938440

[A map of the Philippines can be accessed at http://www.mapsofworld.com/philippines/maps/Philippines-Location.jpg. - Mod.TY]

- Kidapawan City, Cotabato province. 17 Jul 2013. Dengue at least 300; deaths 6; increasing.
http://www.philstar.com/nation/2013/07/17/980791/mayor-recommends-calamity-declaration-dengue-hit-kidapawan

- Negros Occidental province. 20 Jul 2013. Dengue 3304 cases; deaths 10; municipalities most affected: Talisay 336 cases, Silay City 322 cases, Victorias 273 cases, Bago 264 cases, Kabankalan 200 cases.
http://www.visayandailystar.com/2013/July/20/topstory5.htm

- Pangasian province. 19 Jul 2013. Dengue 350 cases; deaths 4; increasing.
http://www.tempo.com.ph/2013/07/2-cases-of-chikungunya-in-pangasinan/#.UewPMq7th9G

Laos. 16 Jul 2013. Dengue 23 470 cases; deaths 69; increasing.
